The paper proposes a method that uses deep learning techniques to accelerate the solution for inverse problems. The proposed method involves learning a conditional denoising auto-encoder and a convolutional neural network, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning (cs.CV, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of matrix inversion and optimization techniques, which are relevant to numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Bayesian strategies and regularization, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
